metadata.reasoningText:
Now I can see the key issue. The CSS uses `nth-child` selectors to create a 2-column grid layout from a virtualized list (which renders items vertically). The CSS transforms move items around:

```css
.agentSessionsWelcome-sessionsGrid .monaco-list-row:nth-child(2) {
    transform: translateX(100%) translateY(-52px);
}
```

This is a fragile approach. When a session is archived (removed from the list), the `nth-child` selectors still apply based on DOM position, but now they're mapping to different items. The CSS transforms will be misapplied.

But the real problem is that the container height is calculated based on the original number of items, and when CSS transforms reposition elements, they can end up outside the visible bounds. When an item gets removed, the container doesn't shrink properly, leaving the whole row hidden. I need to check how the list widget is configured in the TypeScript code to understand the height calculation.

